A system like the conceptual [RABBIT-SOFTWARE repository](https://github.com/ringquistchase-collab/RABBIT-SOFTWARE?utm_source=chatgpt.com) can be designed to work across many operating systems and hardware types, but not “universally” without adaptation. Real-world interoperability depends on drivers, CPU architecture, radio hardware, permissions, networking stacks, and available compute resources.

The best approach is a layered architecture where each layer abstracts hardware differences.

